I'll start by saying I order Tropical Smoothie all the time, and typically I'm happy with the order with only the occasional mix-up. Unfortunately, the past 4 times I've ordered there have been wrong and missing items. Today I got an order that was missing both smoothies. Because I ordered via their website, I have to call the store to get my money back. I've called like 10 times over the past hour and nobody has picked up the phone once. While trying to get a refund, however, I also noticed that the items I typically get were more than what I've been used to. Ordering through the website each item is over a dollar more than they are on other apps and in-store, in addition to the delivery fee, service fee, and tax. I usually love the food here but I'm so beyond frustrated with the service and lack of attention to online orders.

Update: not much was done to “make this right”. I got a scripted email back from the shop owner thanking me for my concern. I’m out $.  OP I attempted to deliver from this restaurant from Uber eats. Unfortunately the packaging was so poor no effort to secure the smoothie was effective to get it the 2.5 miles to the customer. Upon accepting the delivery I didn’t know it’d be a single smoothie provided to me in a paper cup with a piece of plastic wrap loosely placed overtop. Needless to say it didn’t survive, I’m now out the $ and tip I would have earned for delivery, and out another hour of delivery earnings bc I had to return home to clean my insulated bag and clothes.  I recommend not ordering for delivery from here until their packaging is improved. After close to 1000 bike deliveries I’ve only had this type of issue one other time. That was with poorly packaged ramen in a cardboard container.

Never again. I've been a loyal customer who has been I there probably at least twenty times so the food is good but i was definitely turned off today. I ordered my sandwich and I see it being made. Keep in mind there's other mobile orders and other people ordering so maybe it was someone else's. Usually they call out the type of sandwich and the person shows their receipt. I see sandwich preparer making the sandwiches just put it in the mobile order cubby. I ask one of the other employees if that sandwich was for me, and he says no but goes to verify that mine is one of the ones slated to be made. I'm satisfied with that response. But then 20 mins go by and I ask again and the same employee this time asks the lady sandwich preparer about my sandwich. She walks over and grabs the same sandwich I asked about in the first place. I was annoyed that I lost 30 min of time (was on a lunch break). But I was offered no apology from the sandwich maker and only for the employee who really didn't do anything wrong. It was her fault since she never called out the sandwich like for every other order(their system, not mine). But the reason I say never again is because I requested a new sandwich to be made and they provided resistance to that. So I not only deserve to wait a ridiculously long time for a sandwich, but I deserve to pay $12 just to have it cold instead of hot like it's supposed to be. Sounds about right. They reheated it for me.(was nasty reheated btw since it had fresh tomatoes) The whole situation could have been avoided. I saw they were busy so I wasn't trying to pester them but I guess you gotta be on top of your food a these places since no one else is apparently. Tropical smoothie app you have been uninstalled. Potbelly is faster and taste better anyways in my opinion. Not sorry.

Was so excited to have a TroSmo in DC but this place is not as good as others. Customer service is off and smoothies are bland. I recently called in for a pick up order and lady said it should be ready in 20 mins so I get there around 25 mins and it's not made. She takes my order at the register and says she could not make it without me paying. I am a former employee here so I know as well as called other stores for pick up and there has never been a problem. A pick up means that it should be made, in and out. Obviously I was in a rush. Then on top of that the smoothie, a sunny day, which is the easiest smoothie to make was soooo bland, no taste at all. Just straight water. There should be another orientation or some sort to train employees how to properly make smoothies and food.  -former TroSmo manager
